2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimization of resource allocation and power control, which are key topics in information theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an iterative algorithm to obtain a suboptimal solution, which is a common approach in systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions simulation results, which could involve multimedia applications in the heterogeneous network.
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves optimization of user priorities, which could be related to game theory concepts such as utility functions and strategic decision making.
